<headline>Winter Weather Advisory issued December 25 at 6:22PM EST until December 26 at 12:00AM EST by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL MIDNIGHT EST TONIGHT...
* WHAT...Freezing rain. Freezing rain will result in ice
accumulations one tenth of an inch.
* WHERE...Mohawk Valley, the Saratoga Region, and the
Southwestern Adirondacks.
* WHEN...Until midnight EST tonight.
* IMPACTS...Hazardous travel conditions are possible.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Freezing rain could change over or mix with
snow closer towards midnight as precipitation is ending.</description>
<instruction>Slow down and use caution while traveling.</instruction>
